Transport along Molo-Elburgon road in Nakuru County was paralysed for hours on Thursday by youths who were protesting over the poor state of the road.
The angry youths, mostly boda-boda operators, barricaded and lit bonfires along the road.
"We want the area MP Kuria Kimani to come here before we open the road. This road is in poor condition with potholes all over," said one of the protesters.



