Speaking to the Nation, the youths blamed Mr Kimani for the poor state of the road which joins the busy Nakuru- Kericho highway at Mau Summit junction.
Some of the youths dug a wide tunnel along Radi-Sagaitim road which is commonly used by farmers to collect their farm produce from the farms while others blocked Njoro-Elburgon road with stones and twigs.
The youths were later dispersed after police officers arrived and cleared the road.



