But the residents said they will continue protesting until their grievances are heard.
"We recently protested along Radi-Sagaitim road and it was repaired. Let the MP come on the ground and take action," said another resident by the name, John Karanja, who claimed the MP rarely visits the area.
He said a boda-boda operator was recently injured after a vehicle hit a pothole and veered off the road.
